# Kerunity — Cursor Rules (Midnight Glass v1.2)

Read KERUNITY_SPEC.md and DESIGN_SYSTEM_Midnight_Glass_v1.2.md before any changes.

## Design System: Midnight Glass

### Colors (MUST USE)
- Background: #050508 (void), #0a0a0f (bg)
- Gold accent: #f7e1c6 (champagne) — use sparingly
- Emergency: #8a2b3b (deep wine) — 999 button ONLY
- Text: #FFFFFF, rgba(255,255,255,0.9), rgba(255,255,255,0.75)

### Glass Effects (REQUIRED)
- Cards: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(50,55,80,0.6) 0%, rgba(30,35,50,0.7) 100%)
- Backdrop blur: backdrop-filter: blur(12px)
- Borders: rgba(255,255,255,0.08), top edge brighter (0.25 or 0.9 for platinum)

### Touch Targets
- Minimum: 48px
- Standard buttons: 56px
- Crisis buttons (Next, Back, 999): 72px — "Panic Slabs"

### Haptic Motion (ALLOWED)
- Spring easing: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)
- Press state: scale(0.97) translateY(2px)
- Transitions: 0.15s micro, 0.3s larger
- Must respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Hard Rules

### DO
- Follow Midnight Glass design system exactly
- Use glass gradients and backdrop-filter
- Use spring-based haptic feedback
- Keep touch targets large (72px for crisis)
- Preserve all safety guards
- Test offline functionality
- Use system fonts only

### DO NOT
- Use old colors (#161618, #1F1F22, #D4A017, #EB5757)
- Use pure black #000000 (causes halos)
- Use bright red for emergency (use deep wine #8a2b3b)
- Reduce touch targets below minimums
- Remove disclaimers or safety mechanisms
- Add external font/icon CDNs
- Add frameworks or build tools

## Technical
- Main file: /web/index.html
- Plain HTML/CSS/JS only
- PWA with service worker
- No data collection

## Working Style
- Smallest safe change
- Test after each change (Ctrl+Shift+R with cache disabled)
- If broken, revert immediately
- Propose options if unsure

## Definition of Done
- Follows Midnight Glass v1.2
- Touch targets correct (48/56/72px)
- Works offline
- Works with reduced motion
- All buttons functional
